<div class="faq1"><a name="faq01"></a>
<p class="bold">1. What is the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) site?</p>
<p>The Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) is a Web site that provides access, in digital format, to some of the course materials actually used in the University's classes.</p>
<p>The site has two primary objectives:</p>
<ol>
<li>to offer the public at large a glimpse into the University's classrooms by bringing course materials to the Web; and</li>
<li>while helping students engaged in self-directed study, to promote interaction between instructors and students, among instructors themselves, and between instructors and those who are not members of the University community.</li>
</ol>
<p>The Web site is administered by the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare Committee, which was set up in 2005 under the chairmanship of University's Vice-President in conjunction with the establishment of the <a href="http://www.jocw.jp">Japan OpenCourseWare Alliance (JOCW)</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="faq2"><a name="faq02"></a>
<p class="bold">2. Is the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) an on-line university or e-learning program?</p>
<p>No, it is not.</p>
<p>The Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) gives the public access to instructional materials used in certain of the University's courses. It cannot therefore be used to obtain credits toward a degree in any of the University's programs.</p>
</div>
<div class="faq1"><a name="faq03"></a>
<p class="bold">3. What conditions govern use of the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare?</p>
<p>You are free to use the site at no charge for self-directed study. You are likewise welcome to duplicate, distribute, translate, and edit any of the materials at no charge, as long as it is for non-profit, educational purposes. You must, however, give credit to the original author. Please refer to the 
<a title="Legal Notices" href="index.php?lang=en&mode=g&page_type=legal">Legal Notices</a> for details. If you are uncertain whether your intended purpose constitutes non-profit use, please contact <a title="Inquiries" href="index.php?lang=en&mode=g&page_type=inquiry">Inquiries</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="faq2"><a name="faq04"></a>
<p class="bold">4. Who owns the copyright in the courseware posted on the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare site?</p>
<p>The copyright in the courseware posted on the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare site belongs to Nagoya University and the instructors who compiled it. Please refer to the User Guidelines and  the <a title="Legal Notices" href="index.php?lang=en&mode=g&page_type=legal">Legal Notices</a> for details.</p>
</div>
<div class="faq1"><a name="faq05"></a>
<p class="bold">5. Is it OK to create links to the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare site?</p>
<p>Yes, you are welcome to create links from other sites.</p>
</div>
<div class="faq2"><a name="faq06"></a>
<p class="bold">6. If I have a question about something in Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW), can I ask the course instructor directly?</p>
<p>The Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) gives access to the content of University courses, but it does not constitute a course or program in its own right.   Therefore, no direct contact is provided with instructors.</p>
<p>However, members of the public opinions and questions are welcome to submitted via the <a title="feedback" href="index.php?lang=en&mode=g&page_type=feedback">Feedback</a> link</p>
</div>
<div class="faq1"><a name="faq07"></a>
<p class="bold">7. What software do I need to browse the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW)?</p>
<p>To see the course materials, you need Adobe Acrobat Reader. To watch the videos, you need Microsoft's Windows Media Player or RealNetworks' Real Player.</p>
